research/history/logs/agent_action_0035.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With `gated` anchored at `K=128, EF=12, optimizer=signum, lr=1.6e-3`, enabling Hadamard input preprocessing may improve conditioning and smooth the training curve enough to outperform the plain baseline; this round asks only whether `use_hadamard=true` helps the `gated` mainline when all recipe variables except preprocessing are held fixed.","summary":"Round 34 answered the loss-side probe: a small aux term did not improve on the plain `gated` anchor and should be treated as non-helpful for now. Following the requested order, the next single-variable probe is preprocessing. Keep family, K, EF, optimizer, and LR fixed, enable Hadamard rotation with default settings, and judge the result by curve shape as much as terminal FVU. If the run descends more steadily and finishes below `0.149866`, preprocessing is a real lever for `gated`; if it is flat, noisy, or only ties within noise, preserve the plain anchor and avoid further preprocess branching.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, keeps EF fixed at 12, does not touch K, and changes exactly one main variable: preprocessing via `use_hadamard`. It also follows the prescribed sequence by moving to preprocess only after the LR, optimizer, and loss-side probes failed to improve the anchored gated recipe.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"true"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 35 reverts to the plain gated anchor and starts the preprocess-side probe with `USE_HADAMARD=true`.","Read this run by trajectory shape first: if conditioning improves, expect smoother descent and equal-or-better ter